The paper discusses the use of differential privacy as a mathematical tool for guaranteeing generalization in adaptive data analysis, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses concentration bounds for low-sensitivity functions, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper introduces a new approach for proving concentration bounds for high-sensitivity functions, which is a topic related to complexity theory (cs.CC).
